The paper focuses on developing a deep convolutional neural network to rank photo aesthetics, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of joint learning of meaningful photographic attributes and image content information suggests a potential overlap with multimedia (cs.MM) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of a novel sampling strategy to exploit intra-rater consistency, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
